# DispatchSEO self-hosted (docker compose) environment.
#   cp .env.docker.example .env
# Only CRON_SECRET is required - everything else has a sane default or is
# configured later in the dashboard's setup wizard.

# --- REQUIRED ---
# Auth token the cron container uses to trigger scheduled jobs. Generate:
#   openssl rand -hex 24
CRON_SECRET=

# --- Optional ---
# Password for the bundled Postgres. Only set this BEFORE the first boot -
# it is baked into the database volume at creation, and changing it later
# requires wiping the volume (docker compose down -v deletes all data).
# The default is fine for most setups: postgres is only reachable inside
# the compose network, never from the host or the internet.
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=

# The URL your instance is reached at. start.sh fills this in for a local
# trial - only set it yourself for real use: the content pipeline runs
# GitHub Actions in YOUR site's repo, and GitHub must be able to reach this
# URL, so point it at a public domain (reverse proxy) or a tunnel before
# connecting a repo.
# APP_URL=

# Host port the dashboard is published on (container always listens on
# 3000). Leave unset and start.sh picks 3000, or the next free port up if
# something already holds it. Set it to pin a specific port.
# DISPATCH_PORT=

# --- Optional overrides (the setup wizard handles all of these) ---
# DASHBOARD_PASSWORD=
# MCP_API_KEY=
# GSC_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON=
# GSC_SITE_URL=
# DATAFORSEO_LOGIN=
# DATAFORSEO_PASSWORD=
# GH_MERGE_TOKEN=
# RESEND_API_KEY=
# ALERT_EMAIL=
# ALERT_EMAIL_FROM=
# SEED_KEYWORDS=
